But, like every other day, these lofty dreams would have to wait. For now, the problem author sat at his desk as usual, expended a few hours on his usual procrastination run through YouTube, and set to work.

He started typing. Lots and lots of parentheses and square brackets appeared on the screen. Many, many syntax errors happened, the build system screaming at him to just stop and think through what he's doing. He began typing a story, a profound one, one that would truly shock CTF players worldwide with just how remarkably awful it is.